<paragraph id="8BB782EE00012450118BB45C294E58AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="989F945E470ED85CF54BDC1E8F59D2A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Maximum length: ♂ and ♀ 3 mm. Dorsal surface granulated, granules on pereonites 1-7 in two transverse rows, on pleonites 3-5 in one row (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="57C9AAC5FA2CF213F07DF7B897B30426" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27763) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C cephalon, dorsal view. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) D habitus, dorsal view E habitus, lateral view F cephalon, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4D, E</figureCitation>
). Dorsal scale-setae tricorn-shaped in middle segments (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F903BC1700911AB448D7C8F39B322531" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7A</figureCitation>
). Cephalon (Figs 
<figureCitation id="5CA7EDFC5B5B29C03D9A10DF91EFCD3B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27763) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C cephalon, dorsal view. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) D habitus, dorsal view E habitus, lateral view F cephalon, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CF84053C08ADDA761B243F5D6481B6AC" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7B</figureCitation>
) with antennary lobes small, triangular and slightly directed outwards; profrons with suprantennal line bent downwards medially. Pereonites 1 and 2 epimera with postero-lateral corners rounded, 4-7 progressively directed backwards and more acute (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="61940DCCF79BD1FE71268EE8565CF086" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27763) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C cephalon, dorsal view. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) D habitus, dorsal view E habitus, lateral view F cephalon, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4D, E</figureCitation>
). Pleonites 3-5 epimera without glandular pores (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6F6A8CE12673D1EB48F943467197142D" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7C</figureCitation>
). Telson (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3B958AD2EC2CE930930C41E5F7672F71" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7C</figureCitation>
) twice as wide as long, with concave sides and rounded apex. Antennula (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="22790697FD06F3B1437583031C1A3530" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7D</figureCitation>
) with distal article longer than second and first, and bearing at least six aesthetascs plus distal tip. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0848F143F1A8BF0CBEFAEAE1C054F146" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7E</figureCitation>
) with fifth article of peduncle slightly longer than flagellum, bearing one distal strong seta; flagellum of four articles, first and second articles subequal in length, third and fourth articles shorter; apical organ longer than distal article of flagellum. Mandibles as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E2BA3C2F73EB9424B3DF2A16CE4AEA2" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7F, G</figureCitation>
; right mandible with leaf-like lacinia mobilis. Maxillula (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="00C3DDA7D66A24572DD428A19174F898" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7H</figureCitation>
) inner endite with apical penicil robust; outer endite of 4+5 teeth, apically simple, one subapical slender stalk near medial margin. Maxilla as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7F82BFF7AE0968200773F85EE9D722EA" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7I</figureCitation>
. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1196E317962241C4C17B5A2FF8D38E14" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684905" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">7J</figureCitation>
) basis with lateral sides fringed with fine setae; palp with first article bearing two setae, distal articles fused and bearing distal fringe of fine setae; endite much longer than wide, lateral margins covered with fine setae, distal margin bearing two strong setae and one elongated penicil. Grooves and scales for water conducting system on ischium, merus, carpus and propodus of pereopod 6 and basis of pereopod 7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A679B5EDE793EAE158B037ABA9BEFC6" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A uropod (♂, LES 22421) B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 3 exopod G pleopod 4 exopod H pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684906" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">8B</figureCitation>
). Dactylus with ungual seta simple and dactylar seta simple and apically setose. Uropod (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A4D2BBFAC3A126FB4FEA701E0C5441B6" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A uropod (♂, LES 22421) B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 3 exopod G pleopod 4 exopod H pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684906" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">8A</figureCitation>
) protopod and exopod not grooved on sternal margin; exopod longer than endopod and inserted almost at same level.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29A8AC0F4488B99E6EEDA63EC95F5B15" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="4B2D6E5239D562BE2AA2E59F4A47A365" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Male.</emphasis>
Pereopods 1-7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2C804F80EF926311C1708C50C482BF7F" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A uropod (♂, LES 22421) B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 3 exopod G pleopod 4 exopod H pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684906" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">8B, C</figureCitation>
) without any sexual modifications. Genital papilla as in previous species. Pleopod 1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="313B4C7E48FD35379F6E5A4E056F93ED" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A uropod (♂, LES 22421) B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 3 exopod G pleopod 4 exopod H pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684906" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">8D</figureCitation>
) protopod subrectangular, distal margin concave; exopod ovoidal, outer margin almost straight, proximal, inner and distal margins rounded; endopod longer than exopod, basal article short, distal article ca. twice longer than basal one. Pleopod 2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7EB7E4EDE57EDC5217A4E64826377A07" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A uropod (♂, LES 22421) B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 3 exopod G pleopod 4 exopod H pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684906" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">8E</figureCitation>
) exopod ovoidal, twice as wide as long, one seta on inner margin; endopod of two articles, thickset, second article more than three times longer than first, distal portion subquadrangular, distal outer margin with round shaped lobe directed outwards bearing one triangular process on ventral margin. Pleopod 3-5 exopods as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8DB3FB8DD5102D666F7885CD217F0F60" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) A uropod (♂, LES 22421) B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 3 exopod G pleopod 4 exopod H pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684906" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">8F-H</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
